==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: historical
<hw>his*tor"ic*al</hw> <pr>(h⟦icr⟧s*t⟦ocr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>historicus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>"istoriko`s</grk>: cf. F. <ets>historique</ets>. See
<er>History</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to history, or the record
of past events; <as>as, an <ex>historical</ex> poem; the
<ex>historic</ex> page.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>His*tor"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>His*to*ric"i*ty</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> There warriors frowning in <qex>historic</qex> brass.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having once lived, existed, or taken place in the
real world; -- contrasted with <contr>legendary</contr>; <as>as, the
<ex>historical</ex> Jesus; doubt that a <ex>historical</ex> Camelot
every existed; actual <ex>historical</ex> events</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Belonging to the past; <as>as, <ex>historical</ex>
(or historic) times</as>; a <ex>historical</ex> character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Within the period of time recorded in written
documents; <as>as, within <ex>historic</ex> times</as>. Opposite of
<ant>prehistoric</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> diachronic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>diachronic</er>.</def> <ant>synchronic</ant>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Historical painting</b></col>, <cd>that branch of
painting which represents the events of history.</cd> --
<col><b>Historical sense</b></col>, <cd>that meaning of a passage which
is deduced from the circumstances of time, place, etc., under which it
was written.</cd> -- <col><b>The historic sense</b></col>, <cd>the
capacity to conceive and represent the unity and significance of a past
era or age.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Historically</ent>⟦br⟧
